:R-HSA-446210  a            obo:GO_0006048 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "UDP-acetylglucosamine acts as a donor for the first two steps of the N-glycan precursor biosynthesis pathway, and is later used as a substrate for further modifications after the precursor has been attached to the protein. It is synthesized from fructose 6-phosphate, glutamine, acetyl-CoA, and UTP in four steps." ;
